      What are examples of vegetable juices?
      Other popular items in vegetable juices are parsley, dandelion greens, kale, celery, fennel, and cucumbers. Lemon, garlic and ginger may be added by some for medicinal purposes. Other common juices include carrot juice, tomato juice, and turnip juice.

      What is vegetable juice good for?
      Drinking vegetable juice can support your immune system

      Various vitamins, minerals and antioxidants, such as vitamin A, vitamin C, iron, manganese and copper can support your immune system. In most juices, they are well represented, but with a special immunity shot you're sure to get a good dose.      16-Sept-2020
